INSERT INTO `ba_chat` VALUES ('12463', '0', 'AI机器人', '以下是一篇关于海外市场营销研究的国外文献综述：\n\nTitle: A review of research in international marketing\n\nAbstract: The purpose of this paper is to review some key literature in the field of international marketing. It provides an overview of key themes and debates, and highlights some of the most important theoretical and methodological advances of the last decade.\n\nIntroduction:\nInternational marketing has long been an important area of research for scholars interested in exploring the dynamics and complexities of business activities in global markets. Over the years, researchers have explored a wide range of topics, including market entry strategies, cross-cultural differences and similarities in consumer behavior, branding and advertising, and international distribution channels, among others. In this paper, we review some of the most influential research in international marketing, with a focus on theoretical and methodological contributions.\n\nLiterature review:\nWe begin by examining some of the earliest and most influential studies in international marketing. One of the key themes that emerges from this literature is the importance of understanding cultural differences and similarities in consumer behavior. Early scholars, such as Hofstede (198), argued that culture plays a critical role in shaping patterns of consumer behavior, and that marketers must take account of these differences when developing marketing strategies.\n\nAnother important theme in the literature concerns market entry strategies for firms expanding into international markets. Researchers have explored a wide range of issues, including how to select target markets, how to enter new markets, and how to adapt to local market conditions. Johansson and Yip (1994), for example, emphasize the importance of developing a coherent global strategy that balances standardization and adaptation to local conditions.\n\nIn recent years, researchers have increasingly turned their attention to issues related to globalization and the rise of emerging markets. The literature on emerging markets has explored a wide range of topics, including how multinational firms can successfully navigate the challenges and opportunities presented by these markets (e.g., Luo and Tung, 2007), as well as the unique marketing strategies that emerging market firms are adopting to compete in global markets (e.g., Chari and Peppard, 2008).\n\nMethodological advances have also been a key area of focus in recent years. The development of new techniques for analyzing data, such as structural equation modeling and hierarchical linear modeling, has enabled researchers to better understand the complex interactions between different factors that shape international marketing outcomes. In addition, advances in technology have made it easier to collect data from diverse sources, including social media monitoring, online surveys, and mobile research.\n\nConclusion:\nIn conclusion, this paper has reviewed some of the most important and influential research in international marketing, exploring key themes and debates, as well as theoretical and methodological advances. As the world becomes increasingly interconnected and firms continue to expand into new markets, it is likely that research in this area will continue to grow in importance and relevance.', '0', '0', 'gpt-3.5-turbo-0301', null, null, '1683192951');
